trans-unit.source: Represents an access control list (ACL) and is the base class for the <xref href="System.Security.AccessControl.DiscretionaryAcl"></xref> and <xref href="System.Security.AccessControl.SystemAcl"></xref> classes.
trans-unit.target: Representa uma lista de controlo de acesso (ACL) e é a classe base para o <xref href="System.Security.AccessControl.DiscretionaryAcl"> </xref> e <xref href="System.Security.AccessControl.SystemAcl"> </xref> classes.

trans-unit.source: Certain combinations of inheritance and access mask flags are meaningless: - Any access control entry (ACE) with a zero-access mask is removed.
trans-unit.target: Algumas combinações de sinalizadores de máscara de herança e de acesso são sem significado:-nenhuma entrada de controlo de acesso (ACE) com uma máscara de acesso de zero é removida.

trans-unit.source: - Inherit-only ACEs inside object ACLs are removed.
trans-unit.target: -Herdar-só ACEs dentro de ACLs de objeto são removidos.

trans-unit.source: - <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.PropagationFlags>, <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.PropagationFlags>, <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags>, and <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags> flags on all ACEs in leaf object ACLs are cleared.
trans-unit.target: - <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.PropagationFlags>, <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.PropagationFlags>, <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags>, e <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags>sinalizadores em todas as ACEs na folha de objeto ACLs são eliminadas.</xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags> </xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags> </xref:System.Security.AccessControl.PropagationFlags> </xref:System.Security.AccessControl.PropagationFlags>

trans-unit.source: - ACEs that have an <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.PropagationFlags> flag in the absence of the <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags> or <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags> flag are meaningless; they are removed.
trans-unit.target: -ACEs que tenham um <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.PropagationFlags>Sinalizador na ausência do <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags>ou <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags>sinalizador é sem significado; estes são removidos.</xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags> </xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags> </xref:System.Security.AccessControl.PropagationFlags>

trans-unit.source: - The <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.PropagationFlags> flag in the absence of the <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags> or <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags> flag can be removed.
trans-unit.target: -O <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.PropagationFlags>Sinalizador na ausência de <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags>ou <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags>Sinalizador pode ser removido.</xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags> </xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags> </xref:System.Security.AccessControl.PropagationFlags>

trans-unit.source: - ACEs that have an <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.AuditFlags> value of <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.AuditFlags> or <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.AuditFlags> in discretionary access control lists (DACLs) are removed.
trans-unit.target: -ACEs que tenham um <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.AuditFlags>valor <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.AuditFlags>ou <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.AuditFlags>no controlo de acesso discricionário (DACL) de listas são removidas.</xref:System.Security.AccessControl.AuditFlags> </xref:System.Security.AccessControl.AuditFlags> </xref:System.Security.AccessControl.AuditFlags>

trans-unit.source: - Any audit ACE that does not specify either <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.AuditFlags> or <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.AuditFlags> is removed.
trans-unit.target: -Qualquer auditoria ACE que não especifique <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.AuditFlags>ou <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.AuditFlags>é removido.</xref:System.Security.AccessControl.AuditFlags> </xref:System.Security.AccessControl.AuditFlags>

trans-unit.source: - On DACLs, SystemAudit and SystemAlarm ACEs are removed.
trans-unit.target: -No DACL, SystemAudit e SystemAlarm ACEs são removidos.

trans-unit.source: - On system access control lists (SACLs), AccessAllowed and AccessDenied ACEs are removed.
trans-unit.target: -Em listas de controlo de acesso de sistema (SACLs), AccessAllowed e AccessDenied ACEs são removidos.

trans-unit.source: Canonical order is maintained according to the following algorithm: - Explicit ACEs take precedence over inherited ACEs; this rule applies to both DACLs and SACLs.
trans-unit.target: Ordem canónica é mantido, de acordo com o seguinte algoritmo:-ACEs explícitas têm precedência sobre ACEs herdados; Esta regra aplica DACL e SACLs.

trans-unit.source: - In DACLs, among the explicit ACEs, ACEs that deny access take precedence over ACEs that allow access.
trans-unit.target: -In DACL, entre ACEs explícitos, ACEs negarem o acesso precedência sobre ACEs que permite o acesso.

trans-unit.source: For directory object ACLs, the nonobject ACEs come before object ACEs.
trans-unit.target: Para o objeto de diretório ACLs, os ACEs nonobject vêm antes de ACEs do objeto.

trans-unit.source: - All common ACEs take precedence over noncommon ACEs.
trans-unit.target: -Todas as ACEs comuns têm precedência sobre noncommon ACEs.

trans-unit.source: - Inherited ACEs maintain their relative order after canonicity.
trans-unit.target: -Herdados ACEs mantêm a sua ordem relativo após canonicity.

trans-unit.source: - Unrecognized and custom ACEs are disallowed in both DACLs and SACLs.
trans-unit.target: -ACEs não reconhecidos e personalizadas não são permitidos em DACL e SACLs.

trans-unit.source: - Within contiguous ranges (explicit AccessDenied and AccessAllowed ACEs on DACLs, all explicit ACEs on SACLs), the ACEs are sorted by using the <xref:System.Security.Principal.SecurityIdentifier.CompareTo%2A> methods of the <xref:System.Security.Principal.SecurityIdentifier> objects associated with the ACEs.
trans-unit.target: -Nos intervalos de contíguos (AccessDenied explícito e AccessAllowed ACEs no DACL, todas as ACEs explícitos no SACLs), os ACEs são ordenados por utilizar o <xref:System.Security.Principal.SecurityIdentifier.CompareTo%2A>métodos para a <xref:System.Security.Principal.SecurityIdentifier>objetos associados as ACEs.</xref:System.Security.Principal.SecurityIdentifier> </xref:System.Security.Principal.SecurityIdentifier.CompareTo%2A>

trans-unit.source: Adjacent ACEs are combined, if appropriate.
trans-unit.target: ACEs adjacentes são combinados, se apropriado.

trans-unit.source: This reduces the size of the ACL without affecting the access control semantics it grants.
trans-unit.target: Isto reduz o tamanho da ACL sem afetar a semântica de controlo de acesso concede acesso.
